records.addlTxt:
Defendant Miguel R Deleon in court with attorney Matthew Shawn Mayer.  Taylor L. Kraus appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Deputy Court Clerk ssm.  

Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  

Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Defendant sentenced to serve 4 MONTHS in the House of Correction with credit for 2 days time served; Huber privileges for work, child care, school, counseling and medical.  Court STAYED the sentence and placed defendant on Probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 6 MONTHS.
Conditions:
*  AODA assessment/treatment deemed appropriate;
*  Maintain absolute sobriety to be monitored by random urine screens;
*  Maintain full time employment;
*  Perform 20 hours of community service at the rate of 4 hours per month;
*  Pay all costs and surcharges at the rate of $40.00 per month commencing April 10, 2016 or, if not paid, convert to a civil judgment;
*  Submit a DNA sample and pay the DNA surcharge. 
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief received and filed.
